OFFA Descendants Union (ODU), the organisers of the annual ‘Ijakadi festival’ in Offa, Kwara State, said yesterday that the annual cultural event had been fully transformed and capable of promoting Nigeria positively on the international tourism map. The National Public Relations Officer of ODU, Mr. Maruf Ajenifuja, spoke in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Offa. NAN reports that the 2019 Ijakadi Festival, the 8th in the series, will begin on December 24 with environmental sanitation and a special prayer in the community. The festival, with the theme: “A Cultural Revival for Economic Growth”, will end on December 27 with the symbolic cutting of yam.